news.title: Bengaluru: Raghavendra Layout residents oppose factories causing pollution
news.para: Apart from air pollution, residents are also worried about the discharge of chemicals such as grease, paint and oil into the drainage system, which could impact groundwater.

news.title: Swiggy moves to new office in Gurugram, maintain its headquarters in Bengaluru
news.para: Swiggy's main competitor, Zomato, previously operated its headquarters in the same building. However, the company vacated the premises in late 2018.

news.title: Indonesia's central bank to provide funding of $7.9 billion for state housing project
news.para: During last year's election campaign, Prabowo had pledged his government would build 3 million affordable houses per year.

news.title: DM asks fire department to enhance earthquake readiness in Noida
news.para: While seismologists said the earthquake was not of a very high magnitude, its depth of just around 5km and epicentre at Dhaula Kuan in New Delhi, caused stronger reverberations.

news.title: Embassy Developments to raise up to Rs 2,000 crore through QIP
news.para: The fundraising may involve equity shares, convertible or exchangeable securities, Global Depository Receipts, American Depository Receipts, Foreign Currency Convertible Bonds, and other instruments.

news.title: South Delhi’s real estate potential now worth Rs 5.65 lakh crore: Report
news.para: According to the data, around 18,446 plots are available across the 42 Cat A, B & C colonies in South Delhi whose size ranges from 125 sq. yd. to 1750 sq. yd. at an average price of Rs 6- 15 lakh per square yard.

news.title: Baashyam Constructions comes onboard as the associate sponsor for Chennai Super Kings
news.para: A renowned name in the real estate sector, Baashyaam Constructions is known for its innovative approach, cutting-edge design, and exceptional architectural expertise.

news.title: Kolkata civic body demolishes 150 illegal buildings in a year
news.para: The KMC building department lodged 500 FIRs against unscrupulous promoters, said mayor Firhad Hakim on the concluding day of the KMC budget for the financial year 2025-26.

news.title: NCLT admits Ansal API into insolvency proceedings
news.para: IL&FS Financial Services has claimed that the listed Ansal API has failed to honour loans of Rs. 257 crore. It also claimed that Ansal API had entered into a settlement with it in 2022 but was not able to meet the terms of that settlement.

news.title: Seal 19 buildings for flouting rules in Walled City: Rajasthan HC
news.para: The bench of Justice Inderjeet Singh and Justice Manish Sharma gave this interim order while hearing a suo motu cognisance case on commercial activities in the residential area of the city.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body hikes fire safety certificate fee by 10%
news.para: As per the order issued by the MC, buildings of different categories will have to pay fire safety certificate fee at different rates. In Group A category (residential building), lodging houses, hostels, hotels, etc, will have to pay a fee of Rs 6,615 or Rs 14 per square metre.

news.title: CM announces 8.5% interest waiver on premium of self-redevelopment projects in Mumbai
news.para: The govt has allowed the payment of premium in instalments, for which the BMC charges an interest of 8.5%. Fadnavis, who was in Kandivli to inaugurate a residential building redeveloped by the residents through the self-redevelopment route, was apprised of the issue.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh allots Rs 400 crore for Harnandipuram township
news.para: An official privy to developments in Lucknow revealed that the state govt had earmarked Rs 3,000 crore under the scheme, with Rs 1,366.2 crore designated as ‘capital seed' for the township project.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body official suspended for lack of action against illegal constructions
news.para: The proposal to suspend Rokade was under consideration by the administration for 15 days. The suspension action was taken after KDMC chief Indurani Jakhar visited Titwala last month to inspect the ring road project.

news.title: Bengaluru: After complaints, BWSSB to publish builders' Cauvery payment info
news.para: The BWSSB said it will talk to builders who have collected money from homebuyers but have not paid the utility. It said the homebuyers will be free to pursue legal action against the builders who don't pay up even after its intervention.

news.title: Noida: Bhutani Infra fined Rs 5 lakh for illegal excavation
news.para: District mining officer Utkarsh Tripathi said the department received an anonymous complaint regarding unauthorised digging work being carried out in Sector 150.

news.title: Dubai housing market gets a realty check as ED probes rich Indians
news.para: Almost 50% of the buyers in Dubai's prime residential markets are Indians, and many Dubai-based developers and brokerage firms have been hosting property expos in the country to lure customers.

news.title: Godrej Properties 'surprised' by CBI FIR, says not violated any law
news.para: The CBI has alleged that Berkeley Square, developed by Berkeley Realtech Ltd (now known as RSA Motors Pvt Ltd), and Godrej Eternia, developed by Godrej Estate Developers in Chandigarh's Industrial Area, had allegedly violated environmental laws.

news.title: Demerger of Kesoram Industries cement business to be effective from March 1
news.para: The board of UltraTech at its meeting held on Tuesday "declared the scheme (with a swap ratio of 1:52) to be effective from March 1, 2025," the largest cement maker said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Ultratech Cement enters wires and cables segment, to invest Rs 1,800 crore
news.para: ​The plant will be set up near Bharuch in Gujarat and is expected to be commissioned by December 2026, according to a statement from UltraTech Cement.
